g.text: AWS X-Ray is a service that helps you trace and analyze requests in distributed applications.
It allows you to visualize and debug your application's architecture, making it easier to find performance bottlenecks or troubleshoot issues.
* Trace Requests: X-Ray tracks requests as they flow through your applications, including microservices, databases, and other AWS services
* Visualize Architecture: It provides a map of how different parts of your application interact, so you can see where requests are being processed
and where potential delay are occuring.
* Identify Bottlenecks: You can analyze the performance of individual components (e.g which service is slowing down the request) and see how long each
* Debugging: X-Ray shows any errors of exceptions that occurs along the way, helping you troubleshoot issues faster.
* In your code install and import AWS X-Ray SDK: npm install aws-xray-sdk
* Install the X-Ray daemon: It is a software app that listens for trace data sent by X-Ray SDKs running in your application.
It acts as an intermediary between your application and AWS X-Ray service, collecting trace data and submitting it to X-Ray for visualization and analysis
